rkour.com/wp-content/uploads/Essential/wiki/Vauxhall.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1569,1,'2021-03-29 12:46:17','2021-03-29 12:46:17','','Wikis','','publish','closed','closed','','wikis','','','2021-04-04 11:10:49','2021-04-04 11:10:49','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?page_id=1569',0,'page','',0),(1572,1,'2021-03-30 07:05:19','2021-03-30 07:05:19','## Vauxhall\r\n\r\n[Vauxhall Meeting Spot (Sunday Classes)](https://www.google.com/maps/dir//51.4860305,-0.1237323/@51.4860243,-0.1237323,41m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m2!4m1!3e1)\r\n\r\nMeet outside exit 2 of the tube station. At the top of the stairs, we will always be by the big metal barrier and toilets.\r\n\r\n![Vauxhall meeting spot](/wp-content/uploads/Essential/wiki/Vauxhall.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Canada Water - Outdoor\r\n\r\n[Canada Water Meeting Spot (Free class)](https://www.google.com/maps/dir//51.4979044,-0.0492786/@51.4977935,-0.0497355,19.59z)\r\n\r\nThe Free class is also held at Canada Water and the meeting spot is always by the main library building entrance, just outside the tube station. This is next to the wide open area where the food trucks always set up and skateboarders train.\r\n\r\n![Canada Water Outdoor meeting spot](/wp-content/uploads/Essential/wiki/canada-water.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Canada Water - Indoor\r\n\r\n[Canada Water, Seven Islands Leisure Center (Wednesday Class)](https://www.google.com/maps/place/Seven+Islands+Leisure+Centre/@51.4962653,-0.0538746,17.13z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x4876031f8bcda2e3:0xaf374e89873cdc1d!8m2!3d51.4961197!4d-0.0526343)\r\n\r\nThe Wednesday indoor class is held at Seven Islands Leisure Center. It\'s about a 3 minute walk from Canada Water tube station. We meet inside the sports hall.\r\n\r\nAddress is: 100 Lower Rd, Rotherhithe, London SE16 2TU.\r\n\r\n![Canada Water Indoor meeting spot](/wp-content/uploads/Essential/wiki/Seven-Islands.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Class Locations','','publish','closed','closed','','class-locations','','','2021-03-30 08:27:03','2021-03-30 08:27:03','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1572',0,'wiki','',0),(1578,1,'2021-03-30 07:37:03','2021-03-30 07:37:03','![Andy Pearson](/wp-content/uploads/Essential/wiki/andy.jpg)\r\n\r\n## Andy Pearson  Owner, Director & Coach\r\n\r\n-   Creator and Founder of LondonParkour\r\n-   CTO, Senior Coach, Design/Developer, Construction Lead and Shareholder to [ParkourGenerations](http://www.parkourgenerations.com/)\r\n-   [ADAPT Tutor Level 2](http://web.archive.org/web/20170707132637/http://adaptqualifications.com/adapt-certified-database/)\r\n-   [ADAPT Coach Level 3](http://web.archive.org/web/20170707132637/http://adaptqualifications.com/adapt-certified-database/)\r\n-   REPS Qualified\r\n-   Delivered ADAPT Level 1 & 2 Qualifications in:\r\n    -   Boston, Massachusetts, U.S.\r\n    -   Pennsylvania, U.S.\r\n    -   San Diego, U.S.\r\n    -   Tulsa, Oklahoma, U.S.\r\n    -   Bergamo, Italy.\r\n    -   Beijing, China.\r\n    -   Morzine, France.\r\n-   Helped build the original [ADAPTQualifications](http://adaptqualifications.com/) company and its qualifications\r\n-   Helped build the original [ParkourUK](http://parkour.uk/) National Governing Body Organisation\r\n-   Designed & Constructed [the Chainstore](http://chainstoregym.com/) Indoor Parkour Facility\r\n-   [ParkourTactical](http://parkourgenerations.com/tactical/) Team Member\r\n-   Delivered Parkour Classes, as Senior Coach, consistently for over a decade at:\r\n    -   Moberley Sports Indoor Classes\r\n    -   Westminster Academy Adults\r\n    -   Westminster Academy Youth\r\n    -   Sunday Weekend Wakeup Class\r\n    -   Chainstore Beginners Class\r\n    -   Chainstore Balance / Accuracy\r\n-   Parkour Fitness Specialist\r\n-   Delivered to thousands of participants at International Seminars:\r\n    -   Ohio, Columbus, U.S.\r\n    -   Boston, Massachusetts, U.S.\r\n        -   American RDV\r\n    -   Rome, Italy.\r\n    -   Morzine, France.\r\n    -   London, UK.\r\n        -   RDV 3  12\r\n        -   Winterval\r\n        -   Spring Thing\r\n        -   Night Missions\r\n        -   WIPW\r\n        -   Massacre\r\n    -   Glasgow, Scotland\r\n        -   Roots of Movement.\r\n-   ITC Level 2 certified in first aid for sport.\r\n-   Level 4 Award in Preparing to Teach in the life-long Learning Sector\r\n-   Emergency Life Support (RM First Aid Training)\r\n-   Safeguarding and Protecting Children, UK\r\n-   DBS Checked 2019.\r\n-   Registered and Insured by ParkourUK.\r\n-   Certificate in Tutoring sport level 3 (Parkour/Freerunning),UK\r\n-   Mentored the Developing Athlete Program for PKGen','Coaches','','publish','closed','closed','','coaches','','','2021-03-30 08:25:54','2021-03-30 08:25:54','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1578',0,'wiki','',0),(1580,1,'2021-03-30 07:37:40','2021-03-30 07:37:40','Our Code of Conduct at LondonParkour ensures that it is fully committed to safeguarding and promoting the well-being of all its students, ensuring a positive and enjoyable experience for all.\r\n\r\nThe company believes that it is important that members, coaches, administrators and parents associated with the company should, at all times, show respect and understanding for the safety and welfare of others.\r\n\r\nAll students should share any concerns or complaints that they may have about any aspect of the club with Andrew Pearson, Director.','Code of Conduct','','publish','closed','closed','','code-of-conduct','','','2021-03-30 07:52:33','2021-03-30 07:52:33','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1580',0,'wiki','',0),(1582,1,'2021-03-30 07:38:55','2021-03-30 07:38:55','For emailing or contact us, please go to the [contact page](https://londonparkour.com/contact/).\r\n\r\n\r\nFor messaging us, please go to the [@london_parkour](https://instagram.com/london_parkour) instagram channel.\r\n\r\n\r\nAny sensible queries or questions will be responded to within a reasonable amount of time regarding our services, but we value our time and wish to spend it coaching, training and doing parkour!\r\n\r\n\r\nLook through the [support wiki](https://londonparkour.com/support/) and [website pages](https://londonparkour.com/) first before sending your email. Youll find 99% of common queries will already be answered within those pages already.\r\n\r\n\r\nIf time is precious, youll be able to get an answer through these pages faster than an email or message response.\r\n\r\n\r\nAs you are probably aware, there are no phone numbers or email accounts to contact us published on the website. This is to limit the number of communication channels and become quickly overwhelmed as a company. Please use our contact form for any sensible questions.','Contacting us','','publish','closed','closed','','contacting-us','','','2021-03-30 07:52:37','2021-03-30 07:52:37','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1582',0,'wiki','',0),(1584,1,'2021-03-30 07:40:40','2021-03-30 07:40:40','## What do you get?\r\n\r\nWe want to reward our repeat customers and instil a sense of reward for those who are dedicated to their training. Therefore, we are running the following promotional rewards.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Eleven for Ten\r\n\r\nThis is very straight forward. If you purchase one of the Gift-Card 100 discount codes, you\'ll actually get eleven to use. The gift card will track how many uses it\'s had and make sure there is 11, not 10.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## PT Fifty\r\n\r\nFor the truly dedicated, once youve booked and attended fifty London Parkour classes (not including any free ones), we will give you a one-time opportunity to a one-hour Personal Training session with one of our coaches.\r\n\r\nNote that this promotional offer is only valid once per customer.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Blue Light Card\r\n\r\nAs an Emergency Services, NHS and Armed forces BlueLightCard holder, you can claim 10% off any class or PT session. Head over to the [https://www.bluelightcard.co.uk](https://www.bluelightcard.co.uk/) website, log in and search for london parkour to find the discount code. Use the discount code when booking a class on our booking calendar.\r\n\r\nAvailable to:\r\n\r\n44 Response, Ambulance Service, Blood Bikes, Border Force, British Army, Cave Rescue, Community First Responders, Fire Service, Highways Agency, HM Armed Forces Veterans, HM Coastguard, HM Prison Service, Immigration Enforcement, Lowland Search and Rescue, MoD Civil Servant, MoD Fire Service, MoD Police, Mountain Rescue, NHS, Police, Red Cross, Reserve Armed Forces, RNLI, Royal Air Force, Royal Marines, Royal Navy, Search and Rescue, Second Line Responders, St Andrews Ambulance, St John Ambulance, UK Visas and Immigration,\r\n\r\n## Defence Discount Services Card\r\n\r\nAs a Defence Discount Service Card holder, you can claim 10% off any class or PT session. Head over to the [https://www.defencediscountservice.co.uk](https://www.defencediscountservice.co.uk/) website, log in and search for london parkour to find the discount code. Use the discount code when booking a class on our booking calendar.\r\n\r\nAvailable to:\r\n\r\nServing Armed Forces, Reserve Forces, Spouses/Partners of serving personnel, HM Armed Forces Veterans (ex serving), MoD Civil Servants, Bereaved Family Members, War/Service Widow(er)s, Cadet Forces (over 16), NATO Personnel in the UK,\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Booking.\r\n\r\nTo be eligible for these promotions, you must have booked your classes through our class booking system. This is so we have a record of the classes you have attended. We will also give you a stamp-card to get marked everytime you finish a class.','Discounts','','publish','closed','closed','','discounts','','','2021-03-30 07:54:09','2021-03-30 07:54:09','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1584',0,'wiki','',0),(1586,1,'2021-03-30 07:41:22','2021-03-30 07:41:22','LondonParkour respects the rights, dignity and worth of every person and will treat everyone equally within the context of their sport, regardless of age, ability, gender, race, ethnicity, religious belief, sexuality or social/economic status.\r\n\r\nLondonParkour is committed to ensuring that equality is incorporated across all aspects of its development. In doing so it acknowledges and adopts the following [Sport England definition of sports equality](https://www.sportengland.org/about-us/equality-diversity/):\r\n\r\nSports equality is about fairness in sport, equality of access, recognising inequalities and taking steps to address them. It is about changing the culture and structure of sport to ensure that it becomes equally accessible to all members of society, whatever their age, ability, gender, race, ethnicity, sexuality or socio-economic status.\r\n\r\nLondonParkour is committed to everyone having the right to enjoy their sport in an environment free from threat of discrimination, intimidation, harassment and abuse.\r\n\r\nAll students have a responsibility to challenge discriminatory behaviour and promote equality of opportunity.\r\n\r\nLondonParkour will deal with any incidence of discriminatory behaviour seriously, according to our disciplinary procedures.','Equality Policy','','publish','closed','closed','','equality-policy','','','2021-03-30 07:53:46','2021-03-30 07:53:46','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1586',0,'wiki','',0),(1587,1,'2021-03-30 07:41:50','2021-03-30 07:41:50','There are three, easy steps to buying and using gift-cards. Buying, Confirming and Booking.\r\n\r\nEach gift card will have a limit of uses and will become unusable once that amount of bookings have been made.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Step 1  Buying\r\n\r\nOn the [Gift card page](https://londonparkour.com/giftcards/), simply click on the Buy Now button under the specific gift card you wish to purchase.\r\n\r\nThis will popup a Stripe.com payment window.\r\n\r\nThrow in the email address that you wish to use for email confirmation and your credit card details.\r\n\r\nOnce you are sure the details are correct, click the Pay xx.xx Button.\r\n\r\nYou should see the text of the button change to processing and then redirect to the confirmation screen.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Step 2  Confirmation\r\n\r\nOnce the payment has confirmed, you will either get a page with details of any problems with the payment or a thank you page. Rest assured, no payment will be taken if any errors are made. If there is an error, try again from the pricing page.\r\n\r\nYou will be redirected to the Thank You page and be sent a confirmation email with details of the purchase once everything is complete. This page will contain some important information you must keep.\r\n\r\nThere will also be the Stripe Transaction ID for reference and your records.\r\n\r\nOnce the payment has been processed, you will be emailed the coupon code for booking classes. Note, this is a step we have to currently do manually at LondonParkour, so please allow up to 24 hours for us to send you this email.\r\n\r\n**NOTE: If you specify the wrong email address, we will not be able to get in contact with you. If you dont receive your coupon code within 24hours, please use our contact form to find out the status of your order.**\r\n\r\n## Step 3  Booking\r\n\r\nWith your new coupon code, you can use it when booking any class on our class schedule. Simply head over to the classes page, choose the class you want to do, enter your Forename, Surname, Email and Waiver. Then click Book and pay.\r\n\r\nThe payment screen will include a coupon section. Enter your new coupon code and press redeem to see a 100% discount on that class.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Booking Confirmation\r\n\r\nFinally, you should see a confirmation page of your booking with an optional ability to add the appointment to your own personal calendar, as well as a confirmation email to the address given at the start of the booking.','Gift Cards','','publish','closed','closed','','gift-cards','','','2021-03-30 07:54:45','2021-03-30 07:54:45','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1587',0,'wiki','',0),(1588,1,'2021-03-30 07:42:20','2021-03-30 07:42:20','LondonParkour coaches are available to be hired for almost anything from events, seminars and workshops to overseas performances, advertising, stunt work, photo-shoots and tv or movies.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nEvery job is open for negotiation. Please be aware that we will not work with any company promoting a non-holistic or negative lifestyle choice. For example, any association with any alcohol, smoking, fast-food, energy-drink, gambling or unethical manufacturing will be declined.\r\n\r\nWe believe in helping the human species to move and live the way nature intended.\r\n\r\nIf you believe youre making a positive difference to the human race, get in contact.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Contact us\r\n\r\nLet us know the details of your project and head over to our [contact form](https://londonparkour.com/contact/) .','Hiring Us','','publish','closed','closed','','hiring-us','','','2021-03-30 07:56:24','2021-03-30 07:56:24','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1588',0,'wiki','',0),(1592,1,'2021-03-30 07:43:01','2021-03-30 07:43:01','All of the therapists and injury professionals have a first-hand experience and knowledge of parkour and the type of movement it incorporates. They have spent time with LondonParkour and understand the types of injuries specific to the discipline.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Freedom Fit Massage\r\n\r\n**Gemma** at FreedomFit Massage is a Soft Tissue Therapist, MSc, CTHA, ISRM.\r\n\r\n[freedomfit.co.uk](https://www.freedomfit.co.uk)\r\n\r\n![FreedomFit Massage](/wp-content/uploads/Essential/wiki/injury_freedomfit_600x300.gif)\r\n\r\nSoft Tissue Therapy can be used to prevent injury; maintain optimum ranges and quality of movement; rehabilitate from injury/soft tissue damage/post surgery; improve posture; help in optimising alignment throughout the body. All treatments will effectively reduce pain, improve movement and relieve stress. All of these are elements which help to promote health and wellness in body and mind.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Lifestyle Therapies\r\n\r\n**Tom** at Lifestyle Therapies is a level 5 certified sports and remedial therapist.\r\n\r\n[lifestyle-therapies.co.uk](https://lifestyle-therapies.co.uk)\r\n\r\n![lifestyle-therapies](/wp-content/uploads/Essential/wiki/injury_lifestyletherapies_600x300.gif)\r\n\r\nLifestyle Therapies is about a tailored, holistic, approach promising appropriate treatment for every individual who visits us at the LIFESTYLE clinic, with a particular emphasis on education, understanding and movement re-education. You will walk out better than you walked in.','Injury Professionals','','publish','closed','closed','','injury-professionals','','','2021-03-30 08:29:18','2021-03-30 08:29:18','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1592',0,'wiki','',0),(1594,1,'2021-03-30 07:43:47','2021-03-30 07:43:47','# News & Instagram\r\n\r\nIt may seem a little strange that we only post on Instagram, but there is a reason for this. In todays hyper-connected world of so many social media services (Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Vero, etc), messenger applications (iMessage, Snapchat, Facebook Messenger, WhatsApp, etc), and other forms of communication (Blog, Videos, Vlogs, Email, TXT message, Voicemail, Carrier pigeon, flag signals and morse code), weve made the choice that if we use only a single communication channel then every one of our customers knows where to look for news and information.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThis also reduces the miscommunication of conflicting information on different channels. Therefore, at the time of writing, Instagram serves us best because we can post relevant information along with any video or photos that accompany it.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nHowever, since Instagram does not post in a chronological order, this choice may be reassessed at a later time.','Updates','','publish','closed','closed','','updates','','','2021-03-30 07:59:43','2021-03-30 07:59:43','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1594',0,'wiki','',0),(1596,1,'2021-03-30 07:44:21','2021-03-30 07:44:21','## Who will this help?\r\n\r\nEveryone and anyone, including you. The most common mistake we hear is that you need to be fit and healthy already. This is **totally** false and not a prerequisite.\r\n\r\nThe idea is that we are going to give you the coaching, the tools and knowledge to **become** fit, healthy, mobile and functional again.\r\n\r\nIf youre shy, old, overweight, unfit, uncoordinated, injury-prone, have existing injuries or anything else, it doesnt matter at all.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## What benefit is this to you?\r\n\r\nOur private tuition is a face-to-face premium service where you will gain uninterrupted access to one or more of the most experienced parkour coaches in the world. We emphasise this because we are not the best performers, practitioners, competitors, speed runners or anything else However, we have taught many of those types of people.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Experienced\r\n\r\nWe have extended experience since 2005 in instructing Olympic athletes, Special forces soldiers, A-List celebrities, emergency services, seminars, government officials, convicted criminals, people with disabilities or special needs, practitioners in other countries, and much, much more Which makes us uniquely qualified within real practical and functional movement.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## What will you get?\r\n\r\nOur private tuition allows you to focus on any subject you wish to improve practical and functional movement. From overcoming fundamental techniques, understanding strength training, improving your attributes or advice on recovery, assistance work, injury prevention or holistic living. Whatever it is, we can help.\r\n\r\nMaybe you dont have a specific topic, this is OK too The coaches can also take the lead by judging what you would benefit most from.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Im interested! Whats next?\r\n\r\nHead over to our [contact form](https://londonparkour.com/contact/) to request your private session.','Personal Training (PT)','','publish','closed','closed','','personal-training-pt','','','2021-03-30 07:56:33','2021-03-30 07:56:33','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1596',0,'wiki','',0),(1598,1,'2021-03-30 07:44:52','2021-03-30 07:44:52','Photography work, any media or video of any LondonParkour asset, including coaches, logos, classes or events must have the express permission of LondonParkour beforehand.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, any and all work that involves photography or video will require the client to provide all RAW files there-and-then onsite at the end of the work unless express permission in writing from LondonParkour has been made.\r\n\r\nBefore any job, the client will require a method of providing all files to us onsite, there-and-then. Failure to have a method to give us all RAW files will terminate the contract and we will not be able to perform for the photographer/videographer.','Photography & Video','','publish','closed','closed','','photography-video','','','2021-03-30 07:56:37','2021-03-30 07:56:37','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1598',0,'wiki','',0),(1599,1,'2021-03-30 07:45:16','2021-03-30 07:45:16','Your privacy is important to us. It is London Parkours policy to respect your privacy regarding any information we may collect from you across our website, https://londonparkour.com, and other sites we own and operate.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nLondonParkour does NOT store any personal data, electronic information, or banking information on its servers. We do not have user accounts to save information or use any identifyable information on the website.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSharing any personally identifying information publicly or with third-parties, except when required to by law is strictly prohibited by our systems and employees.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nOur website will link to external websites with different policies. Please be aware that we have no control over the content and practices of these sites, and cannot accept responsibility or liability for their respective privacy policies.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nYou are free to refuse our request for your personal information, with the understanding that we may be unable to provide you with some of your desired services.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBy using our website you are accepting our practices around privacy and personal information. If you have any questions about how we handle user data and personal information, feel free to contact us.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThis policy is effective as of 1st January 2021.','Privacy Policy','','publish','closed','closed','','privacy-policy','','','2021-03-30 07:58:12','2021-03-30 07:58:12','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1599',0,'wiki','',0),(1600,1,'2021-03-30 07:45:33','2021-03-30 07:45:33','## Stripe.com\r\n\r\nWe currently use the service stripe.com for all transactions on our class booking pages. Stripe is one of the most recognised and popular online payment methods on the internet today. Powering some of the biggest online services such as microsoft, google, spotify, slack.com and UNICEF, you can trust that any financial transaction is secure.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Drop-ins\r\n\r\nThe traditional way of turning up to class. Check the location of the class on the booking calendar, turn up and pay by cash before the start of the class.\r\n\r\nPlease make sure you have the correct amount, we rarely carry change since most of our bookings and payments are online.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nA Great way to enjoy classes if you have a hectic schedule, are coming from overseas for a short holiday or you just dont know when you can join a session. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Refunds & Returns\r\n\r\nAny booking and payments for a class are non-refundable within 48 hours of that booking. Once a booking has been made, you are reserving your position in that class and therefore restricting others from booking.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nA gift card is refundable as long as it has not been used for any bookings and has been purchased within 14 days. Please contact us with the contact form for further information on this process.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nAll other services require payment up-front by the customer and are only refundable if we are unable to complete the job due to our own negligence or inability. Any cancellations from the customer, issues regarding the service being changed by the customer, or anything else not within the control or power of LondonParkour to provide the service advertised and agreed upon will not provide a refund.','Pricing','','publish','closed','closed','','pricing','','','2021-03-30 07:57:51','2021-03-30 07:57:51','',0,'https://dev.londonparkour.com/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=1600',0,'wiki','',0),(1604,1,'2021-03-30 07:46:09','2021-03-30 07:46:09','## Responsibility\r\n\r\nI agree that any claims of disability (permanent or otherwise), injury to oneself, liabilities from death or loss of any kind are waived when participating in a London Parkour activity. I agree to full liability of any kind and free any London Parkour staff member of any claims.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Equipment\r\n\r\nBy agreeing to this waiver I also consent to full responsibility for any personal injury, death or damage to equipment through the use of any London Parkour apparatus, structures, equipment or facilities during any London Parkour activity.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Injury\r\n\r\nI accept and understand that training parkour has risks and dangers associated with it. This includes any participation of any London Parkour classes or taking instruction from London Parkour coaches.\r\n\r\nI waive my rights to hold any London Parkour coach, instructor or teacher liable for any level of injury that may occur while engaging in a class or parkour activity under London Parkour.','Student Waiver','','publish','closed','closed','','student-waiver','','','2021-03-30 07:58:59','2021-03-30 07:58:59','',0,